properties.notes: Good sidewalks and relatively few street crossings. Lots of hotels. Two Denny's.
Along Highway 99. Sidewalks are good, though narrow when passing over Highway 518. More hotels.

Charming Tukwila suburbs and glimpses of the Duwamish. Boeing Access Road section mile 3.25 to mile 3.80) has worst pedestrian conditions of the entire route. Section west of I5 requires crossing the on/off ramps to Airport Way S. Use the signalled crossing to switch from south to north side of Boeing Access Road. The portion directly over I5 is in a shoulder lane. Use extreme caution.

properties.name: Dangerous Crossings
properties.comment: Follow route and crossings carefully. Use shoulder of Boeing Access Rd until bridge. Access ramp crossings are unmarked and dangerous. Use north side shoulder approaching MLK Way.
properties.description: Follow route and crossings carefully. Use shoulder of Boeing Access Rd until bridge. Access ramp crossings are unmarked and dangerous. Use north side shoulder approaching MLK Way.

properties.notes: Good, wide sidewalk.
Good, wide sidewalk. MLK is built up in this area.
Good, wide sidewalk. MLK is built up in this area.
Mostly residential with okay sidewalks. Mind the climb.
Beacon Ave is a commercial corridor with good sidewalks. Good views of West Seattle as you drop into SODO.
Entirely on the SODO trail, a dedicated multi-use pathway that runs along the Link and the busway. Enjoy the SODO Track murals.
Fair sidewalks, mostly by parking lots for industrial businesses.
Urban core environment with frequent crosswalks. Large sidewalks.
Dense urban environment with frequent crosswalks. Mainly through retail corridors.

Pike Place Market is a great half-way spot for coffee! The route gets close enough on Pike that you'll be able to spot the iconic sign for a team photo. Note weekend mornings at the market are crowded. Expect another 10 minutes if you detour and run through.
Good sidewalks throughout. Steep climb.
Gentle climb through a residential area. Beware root-heaved sidewalks. Steep descent through the beautiful Interlaken park, followed by a short climb up stairs along 22nd Ave. E.
Soak in Rainier Vista, Red Square, and the tree-lined Memorial Way. Good sidewalks throughout. Fair climb. There are stairs leading up to Red Square, though a ramp is available.
Expect crosswalk slowdown before reaching Roosevelt Way NE. Semidense with lowrise apartments and townhomes. Sidewalks are good along Roosevelt Way.
Largely residential with nice trees. Beware root-heaved sidewalks with significant leaf cover. Mind the climb.
A couple long crosswalk waits. Slips by Kraken Iceplex before turning into mild rolling sidewalks. Trail along the golf course is surprisingly secluded.

properties.name: Construction
properties.comment: Expect minor detours around NE 145th St.
properties.description: Expect minor detours around NE 145th St.

properties.notes: Rolling hills and fair sidewalks.
NE 188th St is steep and has no sidewalks. The crossing over 15th Ave NE to get back on the sidewalk is unmarked. The remainder is on fair sidewalks.

properties.name: Unmarked Crossing
properties.comment: NE 188th St has little space for pedestrians. Crossing onto 15th Ave NE is not marked or signalized. Use caution.

properties.notes: Quiet suburbs. Passes several schools and parks. The two blocks along 216th St SW are on a shoulder. Finishes on a paved section of the Interurban Trail.
